==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin, a crab. Applied to cancerous tumors because the enlarged veins ressembled the legs of a crab.

===Noun===
'''cancer'''
# a disease where the cells of various body tissues begin uncontrolled (and often rapid) proliferation

